	<div class="related-portal-div">
	   <H2>Related Resources:</H2>
	   <p>Many affiliated web portals are secure areas only accessible to registered users affiliated with a member institution of the Australian Access Federation. To check if your institution is a member refer to the <a href="http://www.aaf.edu.au/index.php/join/member-institutes/">AAF website</a>. If you would like to register please use the appropriate link below and follow the instructions.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="related-portal-div">
	<h3>Virtual Rock Laboratory</h3>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p>	The Virtual Rock Laboratory is a web portal that allows running <a href="https://launchpad.net/esys-particle">ESyS-Particle</a>
	Discrete Element (DEM) simulations on the ARCS/AuScope computational Grid.
	For more information about the Virtual Rock Laboratory please go to the
	<a href="https://twiki.auscope.org/twiki/bin/view/Grid/ProjectVRLUserGuide">Virtual Rock Lab User's Guide</a>.
	</p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p>
	To access the Virtual Rock Laboratory now, please follow this link:  <a href="https://portal.esscc.uq.edu.au/vrl">Virtual Rock Laboratory</a>
	</p>
	</div>

	<div class="related-portal-div">
	<h3>Escript Portal</h3>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p>The Escript Portal is a web portal that allows running <a href="https://launchpad.net/escript-finley">Escript/Finley</a>
	  Finite Element (FEM) simulations on the ARCS/AuScope computational Grid.
	  For more information about the Escript Portal please refer to the <a href="https://twiki.esscc.uq.edu.au/bin/twiki/view/ESSCC/EscriptPortalUserGuide">Escript Portal User's Guide</a>.</p>
	<p>&nbsp; </p>
	<p>To access the Escript Portal now, please follow this link: <a href="https://portal.esscc.uq.edu.au/escript">Escript Portal</a>
	</p>
	</div>

	<div class="related-portal-div">
	<h3>Geodesy Workflow Portal</h3>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p>The Geodesy Workflow is detailed <a href="https://twiki.auscope.org/wiki/bin/view/Grid/ProjectOverviewGeodesyWorkflow">here</a>. It allows users to discover, select, and process geodetic data from around Australia on HPC facilities.</p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p>To access the Geodesy Workflow portal now, please follow this link: <a href="https://auscope-portal-2.arrc.csiro.au/GeodesyWorkflow">Geodesy Workflow Portal</a></p>
	</div>

	<div class="related-portal-div">
	<h3>Centre for 3D Mineral Mapping Portal (C3DMM)</h3>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p>The Centre for 3D Mineral Mapping Portal is detailed <a href="https://twiki.auscope.org/wiki/bin/view/Grid/ProjectOverviewGeodesyWorkflow">here</a>. It allows users to view and consume hyperspectral derived products and data from around Australia.</p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p>To access the C3DMM portal now, please follow this link: <a href="http://c3dmm2.ivec.org/">Centre for 3D Mineral Mapping Portal</a></p>
	</div>

	<div class="related-portal-div">
	<h3>Virtual Exploration Geophysics Laboratory (VEGL)</h3>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p>The Virtual Exploration Geophysics Laboratory is detailed <a href="https://www.seegrid.csiro.au/wiki/bin/view/ASRDC/VEGLProject">here</a>. It allows users to discover, select, and process geophysics data from around Australia on HPC facilities.</p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p>To access the Virtual Exploration Geophysics Laboratory now, please follow this link: <a href="https://auscope-portal-2.arrc.csiro.au/VEGL-Portal">Virtual Exploration Geophysics Laboratory</a></p>
	</div>

	<div class="related-portal-div">
	<h3>Bureau of Meteorology Portal</h3>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p>The Bureau of Meteorology Portal is detailed <a href="https://www.seegrid.csiro.au/wiki/bin/view/ASRDC/BoMDeploymentProject">here</a>. It allows users deep access into the Bureau of Meteorology data archive, and presents it back to the user via the interface.</p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p>To access the Bureau of Meteorology Portal now, please follow this link: <a href="https://auscope-portal-2.arrc.csiro.au/BOM-Portal">Bureau of Meteorology Portal</a></p>
	</div>

	<div class="related-portal-div">
	<h3>Minerals Down Under (MDU) Earth Model</h3>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p>The MDU Earth Model is detailed <a href="https://twiki.auscope.org/wiki/bin/view/Grid/ProjectOverviewGeodesyWorkflow">here</a>. MDU's Earth model is a collection of open file data, MDU generated open data, and MDU's internal data collections. This covers a wide range of data types not exposed in the AuScope portal. It requires an AAF credential to see all available data. </p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p>To access the MDU Earth Model portal now, please follow this link: <a href="http://mdu-data.arrc.csiro.au/portal">MDU Earth Model</a></p>
	</div>
